<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870717-0047 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Boeing Co.</HL><DD> 07/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BA FRESTAEROSPACE (ARO) </IN><TEXT>   Boeing Co. acknowledged that it is in negotiations with the government of Taiwan on the purchase of six 747-400 jumbo jets. Seattle-based Boeing was responding to news reports that the Taiwanese government is planning to buy the planes for about $1 billion to help satisfy a $2.28 billion trade commitment with the U.S. A Boeing spokesman said the aerospace and defense company doesn't disclose prices until sales are completed. </TEXT></DOC>